comments: Johnson (PHX) and Wright (DET) make incidental arm contact with one another as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.

Grant (DET) and Booker (PHX) make incidental contact with one another as they attempt to retrieve the ball, some of which occurs to Booker's head.  Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Johnson (PHX) jumps towards Wright (DET), who is drifting away from the basket and marginal contact occurs to his leg during his driving shot attempt.
Ayton (PHX) and Griffin (DET) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Griffin (DET) firms up in his screening position following the hand-off and absorbs the contact made with Bridges (PHX).
Ayton (PHX) extends his right hand against Grant's (DET) side and initiates contact that affects Grant's driving shot attempt.
Griffin (DET) has his hands on Bridges' (PHX) side before quickly sliding them off.
Plumlee's (DET) left forearm is extended forward when marginal contact occurs with Paul's (PHX) front inside the perimeter.
Paul (PHX) extends his leg unnaturally into Plumlee (DET) during the jump shot attempt and affects his ability to defend the play.

Ayton (PHX) is extending his hand to retrieve the ball when some contact occurs with Griffin's (DET) face during rebounding. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Bridges (PHX) cleanly deflects the ball away from Bey (DET).
There is no clear and conclusive video evidence that Griffin (DET) makes contact to Bridges' (PHX) arm during his jump shot attempt.
Griffin (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Bridges' (PHX) path and does not deliver the contact.
Ayton (PHX) maintains legal guarding position and absorbs the body contact made with Grant (DET) at the end of the drive.
Grant (DET) commits the take foul on Booker (PHX).
Bey (DET) and Crowder (PHX) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Ayton (PHX) and Grant (DET) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Ayton (PHX) has his hand extended forward when marginal contact occurs with Wright (DET) during his drive into the lane.
Bey (DET) brushes Booker's (PHX) right arm and marginal contact occurs after his gather.
Saric (PHX) jumps vertically and absorbs the body contact made with Grant (DET) during the driving shot attempt.
Plumlee (DET) and Johnson (PHX) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Ayton (PHX) has his hand extended forward as marginal contact occurs with Wright (DET) during his drive into the lane.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Grant's (DET) path and does not deliver the contact.
Bey (DET) briefly has his arm around Booker's (PHX) midsection before sliding it off.
Plumlee (DET) is moving forward slightly when marginal body contact occurs with Paul (PHX) along the perimeter.
Paul (PHX) attempts to commit the take foul on Wright (DET) and the contact is marginal.
Paul (PHX) commits the take foul on Wright (DET).
Carter (PHX) briefly has his hands on Grant's (DET) hips before quickly removing them.
Paul (PHX) commits the take foul on Grant (DET).
